comment:
* A single entry retrieved from the drop box.
     * This may include a reference to a stream, so you must call
     * {@link #close()} when you are done using it.

methods.name: public void close()
methods.comment: Close the input stream associated with this entry.

methods.name: public String getTag()
methods.comment: @return the tag originally attached to the entry.

methods.name: public long getTimeMillis()
methods.comment: @return time when the entry was originally created.

methods.name: public int getFlags()
methods.comment: @return flags describing the content returned by {@link #getInputStream()}.

methods.name: public String getText(@BytesLong int maxBytes)
methods.comment:
* @param maxBytes of string to return (will truncate at this length).
         * @return the uncompressed text contents of the entry, null if the entry is not text.

methods.name: public InputStream getInputStream() throws IOException
methods.comment: @return the uncompressed contents of the entry, or null if the contents were lost

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel out, int flags)
